claim.claim-text:
6. An apparatus for use in performing channel estimation on an orthogonal frequency division multiplexing (OFDM) system, comprising:
a receiver configured to receive a transmitted OFDM signal;
a pilot symbol extractor configured to extract pilot symbols from the OFDM signal; and
a channel estimator configured to:
choose reserved tones to be part of a pilot pattern;
use a projection of signal peaks onto the reserved tones to produce a reduction signal;
use the reduction signal for peak canceling to lower a peak to average power ratio; and
use the reserved tones in the pilot pattern to perform the channel estimation.
